Xinhua Times Commentary: Turning outstanding returned migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talent is the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
Outstanding migrant workers returning to their hometowns are an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency published Hai Chun
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, whose family is in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan, quit his job in Beijing in 2010 with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned to his hometown to start a business.
After several years of hard work, he now runs a grape planting family farm with an annual income of more than one million yuan, becoming a well-known leader in getting rich, and has also been selected to join the team of the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, under the encouragement and inspiration of a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit farmers, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return to their hometowns to start businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries were produced, 61,000 village reserve forces were cultivated, and more than 20,000 party members were developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Whether you are well-off or not, the key depends on your fellow countrymen.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in China's rural areas have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively it has also led to the emergence of "hollowing" in rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grassroots organizations, and the secretaries of village party branches and party members have shown the characteristics of "one old and one low", that is, they are aging and have low educational qualifications, and the team of leaders of village party organizations is not strong, and the problem of lack of young and yellow people is prominent.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing to the city in one direction, and the countryside has been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is an empty word.
Attracting those peasant workers who are capable, conscious, and interested in serving their hometowns back, guiding them to return to their hometowns to start businesses and become leaders in getting rich, selecting the best from them to train them to become party members and rural cadres, and enriching the ranks of grassroots cadres is the fundamental policy to solve the problem of the shortage of rural party members and grassroots party organizations.
If outstanding migrant workers can be brought back, they must be retained and do a good job.
In recent years, Sichuan has started with the party building of migrant workers, and on the basis of strict selection standards, it has established institutional mechanisms such as targeted referral, service guarantee, training and improvement, and selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their ability, work security, and hope for life, and truly take root in the countryside and have a sense of accomplishment in entrepreneurship.
This year is the final year of the decisive battle against poverty, and talent is the key factor in the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding migrant workers who have returned to their hometowns, and through comprehensive measures, build them into a task force and a new force that can be retained, can fight, and cannot be taken away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural areas to get rid of poverty and become moderately prosperous and revitalize their development.
