Nantes church fire in France: parish volunteers admit arson, usually kind and silent-chinanews.com
Chinanews.com, July 26 According to foreign media reports, on July 18, the famous Cathedral of St. Peter and St. Paul, a religious and historical architectural treasure in Nantes, France, was seriously damaged in a fire, and the large pipe organ was completely destroyed.
On the 26th local time, the Nantes prosecutor announced that a parish volunteer who was in charge of guarding the cathedral had been indicted for "arson and destruction".
He has confessed that he was the one who lit the fire in the church.
According to the report, local prosecutor Senas said that the 39-year-old parish volunteer from Rwanda admitted that he lit three fires in the cathedral at night.
The man's lawyer said the arsonist now regretted doing the thing.
This person had been evacuated to France a few years earlier, where he was sheltered in the parish where the fire occurred and taken in in a church.
The prosecution pointed out that recently, he tried to renew his visa and was in dialogue with the police about it.
But the church said it still couldn't believe that this believer, who was usually very kind and smiling, but didn't talk much, would destroy the church he loved so much.
On the day of the fire on July 18, the volunteer had already been questioned by the police for a logical problem in his account, but he was later released.
The picture shows firefighters at the scene for rescue.
On the evening of the 25th, the person was again arraigned as the professional engineers of the laboratory of the Central Police Department in Paris obtained new evidence.
This time, the man confessed to his act of arson.
According to reports, if convicted of intentional arson, the suspect could face 10 years in prison and a fine of 150,000 euros.
According to the report, the fire caused serious damage to the cathedral of Saint-Pierre and Saint-Paul, the pipe organ in the church was completely burned down, and the stained glass windows behind the pipe organ were also seriously damaged.
According to Brunet, the chief architect of the French historic building, it is conservatively estimated that the restoration of the Nantes Cathedral will take at least three years.
Comprehensive news: U.S. unilateralism undermines relations between the two countries, and international public opinion supports China's countermeasures against the United States-Xinhuanet
Beijing, July 26 (Xinhua) -- On the morning of July 24, the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs informed the U.S. Embassy in China that China had decided to revoke the permit for the establishment and operation of the U.S. Consulate General in Chengdu and put forward specific requirements for the Consulate General to cease all operations and activities.
International public opinion believes that the unilateral measures taken by the United States have caused serious troubles in Sino-US relations, and that it is legitimate and necessary for China to respond to the unreasonable provocation of the United States and to take countermeasures.
Andrés Bolkes, director of the Center for Chinese Studies at the Institute of International Studies at the University of Chile, said that the unilateralist measures of the United States have destroyed the bridge of understanding between the Chinese and American peoples and caused a crisis in the relations between the two major countries.
China's notification to the United States of the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a countermeasure to the unilateral measures taken by the United States and is in line with diplomatic practice.
Patricio Giusto, a professor at the Pontifical Catholic University of Argentina and director of the Center for Arab-Chinese Studies, believes that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary countermeasure to the previous provocations of the United States, and is not aimed at ordinary Americans.
The U.S. is trying to distract the U.S. public by pressuring China to cover up its ineffective response to the pandemic.
Bambang Suryono, chairman of the Asian Innovation Research Center, an Indonesian think tank, said that the provocative diplomatic posture adopted by the United States has caused serious troubles to Sino-US relations, and the relations between the two countries are facing severe challenges.
China's notification to the United States that the closure of its Consulate General in Chengdu is a normal countermeasure that is in line with diplomatic practice, which not only reflects China's principled position of resolutely safeguarding its own interests, but also reflects the reasonableness, advantage, and restraint of China's diplomacy.
Tanzanian current affairs commentator Francis Semwinza said that China's decision is a legitimate and necessary response to US provocations.
For China-US relations to return to normal, the US should take the initiative to improve relations with China and stop interfering in China's internal affairs.
The United States should focus on how to achieve economic and political win-win results with China, and how to benefit the people of both countries and the international community as a whole.
Ali Youssef, executive director of the Sudan-based Federation of Arab-Chinese Friendship Associations, said that the countermeasures that China is forced to take are a legitimate and necessary response to the unreasonable actions of the United States, which are in line with international law and basic norms governing international relations, as well as diplomatic practices.
Earlier, the US side demanded the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, which seriously violated international law and basic norms governing international relations.
It is hoped that the US side will revoke its previous decision and create the necessary conditions for the return of bilateral relations to normal.
Singapore's "Lianhe Zaobao" published an editorial saying that the greater strategic intention of the United States is to contain China and prevent China from continuing to rise.
In the face of the United States' step-by-step pressure, although China is very reluctant to see Sino-US relations continue to deteriorate, it has no choice but to take countermeasures.
