The upgraded version of the Russian helicopter gunship Ka-52M left the factory for the first time at the end of the year-Xinhuanet
Moscow, 25 Jul (Xinhua) -- According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the Ka-52M, an upgraded version of the Ka-52 helicopter gunship (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi), will be renovated and reequipped for the first time in December this year and will leave the factory.
According to Russia's "Izvestia" a few days ago, the Wuzhi Ka-52M is called "Super Alligator", and its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year, and the first batch of 2 of the upgraded Wuzhi is being modified and refitted at the Far East Helicopter Factory of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Group Corporation, and its national testing and improvement will be completed before October 2022.
It is understood that the above upgrade work of Russian experts introduced, "super alligator" of the "predecessor" - Wu Zhika-52 in November 2011 officially installed, the model in use exposed some weaknesses, the upgrade is to "make up for the shortcomings".
According to the report, compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will be partially made of new protective materials that will not increase its weight, and its pilot's cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of surviving on the battlefield; it will be equipped with a more powerful generator to provide power to more complex airborne electronic equipment; and the optoelectronic system will be upgraded to be capable of reconnaissance, Identifying battlefield targets that are farther apart; equipped with a new type of light multi-purpose missile that mainly attacks armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications, has a range of up to 20 kilometers, which is about twice the range of similar missiles used by Russia's current armed forces; and its defensive weapons and communications equipment will be used to the greatest extent possible with the Mi-28NM helicopter gunship that can attack air targets, so that the relevant maintenance will be simple and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have a more advanced electronic guidance system, weapon sighting system and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with the drone, so as to obtain the intelligence transmitted by nearby drones in real time in the air, such as displaying images taken by the drone on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the Ka-52M pilot will be able to directly control the UAV that cooperates with it, thereby improving the pilot's grasp of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoy Ruchko said in December last year that the Russian Ministry of Defense plans to purchase more than 110 Wuzhika-52M by 2027.
