Since the beginning of this year, Hebei has provided 1.75 billion cubic meters of ecological water supply to rivers and lakes
Shijiazhuang, 26 Jul (Xinhua) -- This reporter learned from the Hebei Provincial Department of Water Resources that since the beginning of this year, Hebei Province has made overall use of water from the diversion of rivers and water from local reservoirs to successively carry out ecological water replenishment to 28 rivers such as the Hutuo River, Tang River, and Juma River, as well as Baiyangdian Lake, and has completed a total of 1.75 billion cubic meters of ecological water replenishment of rivers and lakes.
Hebei Province has seized the favorable opportunity of increasing the flow of water conveyed by the middle route of the South-to-North Water Diversion Project, and has implemented ecological water replenishment to the Tanghe, Shahe, and Zhulong rivers by diverting water from the river.
At the same time, nine large and medium-sized reservoirs such as Xidayang and Tobushi and Baiyangdian Lake have been used to implement ecological water replenishment to rivers such as Fuyang River and Qinglong River, with a cumulative water surface area of more than 90 square kilometers.
In order to do a good job in ecological water replenishment, the Hebei Provincial Department of Water Resources actively organized and carried out the investigation, remediation and reinforcement of water replenishment rivers and river cleaning, refined practical measures, and strengthened inspection and management.
Through supervision and inspection and centralized unannounced visits, various problems were solved in a timely manner to ensure the safety and orderliness of river water replenishment.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Hebei Provincial Department of Water Resources, the orderly implementation of the ecological water replenishment of rivers and lakes has effectively restored the ecological environment of rivers and lakes in Hebei Province, promoted the replenishment and conservation of groundwater along the coast, and greatly improved the living environment and economic development environment along the line, which is of great significance to the realization of the river and lake management and protection goals of "clear water, green banks, smooth rivers and beautiful scenery".
