"Plugging the Jiangnan" in pursuit of the poetic "Yellow River Dream"-Chinanews.com
(China's Poverty Alleviation Story) "Plugging the Jiangnan" in pursuit of the poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Service Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River is thousands of miles of sand, and the waves are blowing from the end of the world. ”
The Yellow River, which has aroused the pride of countless literati, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain, and now, Ningxia, which is known as "plugging the south of the Yangtze River", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The "Dream of Blue Waves" with beautiful rivers and clear waters
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia", the Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers, and is the "mother river" of the nurturing party.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, there is an imbalance between the development and utilization of rivers and lakes and the management and protection, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, land reclamation of lakes and encroachment on water areas has become prominent, resulting in black and odorous water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
At present, Ningxia is promoting the restoration of water ecology and striving to restore the Yellow River.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government has adopted the method of "upgrading + pollution control + strict management", and all the sewage in the industrial park has been centrally treated, and all the urban sewage treatment plants have been discharged according to the first-class A standard, and the black and odorous water bodies in the urban built-up areas have been basically eliminated, and the third batch of China's black and odorous water demonstration cities have been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and river and lake chief patrols have become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, who lives in a village near the Yellow River, has witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The water used to smell bad, but after the remediation, the smell is gone. ”
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better, his life is more comfortable, and now he often goes to the Yellow River with his family for a walk to feel the clear water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sand Gull Xiangji
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water...... Fan Zhongyan's beautiful scenery of "sand gulls soaring" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia and forms a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands along the way, which play an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance, and also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, Ningxia departments have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects, and at present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, nearly 200 natural lakes and swamp wetlands, 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, and 8 municipal-level parks.
Lv Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Conservation Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds, "The relict gull is an endangered bird, there are only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 inhabit the Yinchuan wetland." ”
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a red line of 500 meters in the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that no unit or individual shall carry out development, construction or business activities within the protected area except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through the treatment of pollution sources, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of nine major drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached 100% of the Class IV standard. ”
The "Drinking Water Dream" of Benefiting People's Livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an "embarrassing" title: it was the only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River and lacked water to drink".
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the problem of continuous water shortage during the peak summer season, and the "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become the painful summer experience of many high-rise residents, but under the current situation that the major water sources are at the limit of over-exploitation and a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel has been formed under the urban underground, the water-source water shortage has become a problem that plagues Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking the purified Yellow River water has become a good solution to the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Municipal Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan for domestic production and production, Ningxia launched the water supply project of the western line of urban and rural areas in the Yinchuan metropolitan area in a timely manner, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
On December 29, 2019, the water supply project was officially opened to the three districts of Yinchuan City, and in 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the water of the Yellow River. ”
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply, "the next step, we will integrate the scattered water supply points in the countryside and connect all to the west line water supply project, and it is expected that the urban and rural integrated water supply in Yinchuan will be basically realized by the end of this year." ”
