Shenzhen solicits public opinions on the introduction of health regulations-Xinhuanet
Shenzhen, 26 Jul (Xinhua) -- Residents are encouraged to undergo physical examinations to detect problems as soon as possible; the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited; a health review system for online games is established; and employers are required to appoint full-time and part-time health management personnel...... A few days ago, the "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comments)" was officially released, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and detect problems as soon as possible, the above-mentioned draft proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination items based on factors such as age and occupation.
The cost of health examination within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the social medical insurance pooling fund according to the standard of once a year per person.
The Consultation Paper clarifies that employers should reasonably allocate human resources, arrange work and rest time for employees, and implement a rotation leave system for employees with heavy mental and physical labor loads, so as to avoid excessive wear and tear of human body functions or physical and mental health injuries to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers should appoint full-time and part-time health management personnel, and organize regular health examinations for employees.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft proposes to prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors, and at the same time restricts the location of alcoholic beverages, and for those who violate the regulations, the market supervision and management department will order corrections and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "abstaining from alcohol", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the draft for comments, schools should arrange for students to spend more than one hour of physical activity each day.
With regard to online games, departments such as for public security, culture, radio, television, tourism, sports, online regulation, and health shall improve systems for the health supervision of internet access service business sites, establish systems for the health review of online games, and create a positive space and culture of communication for promoting the healthy growth of young people.
In addition, the draft also proposes that flu patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions will be fined 20,000 yuan for leaking patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that all departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents involving urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization, ecological environmental protection, and biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
Where it has not been assessed or will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health, it must not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
