China News Service, Hami, Xinjiang, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Xinjiang is deeply cultivating "sunflower fields" and making good use of clean energy
More than 6,000 pentagonal heliostats, each of 48 square meters, are arranged neatly in a circle, like a silver "sunflower field", which rotates with the sun and reflects the sunlight to the center of the heat absorption tower more than 200 meters high to achieve power generation.
The reporter saw this scene on the 25th at the Hami molten salt tower solar thermal power plant of the China Power Project in Naomaohu Town, Yiwu County, Hami City, Xinjiang.
"The so-called molten salt tower solar thermal power generation is to reflect sunlight to the heat absorption tower through the mirror surface to form heat energy, and then convert the heat energy into electrical energy through traditional power generation technology. ”
Daniel Zhang, deputy general manager of CLP Hami Solar Thermal Power Co., Ltd., said that the design principle is similar to that of solar cookers used in rural areas in northwest China, which all gather sunlight.
The plant started construction in October 2017 and was connected to the grid at the end of last year, covering an area of 6,600 acres, with a total of 14,500 heliostat mirrors planned to be installed.
"The biggest advantage over conventional solar power generation technology is that it can store the accumulated heat energy and generate electricity at night. ”
Daniel Zhang said that the 13-hour heat storage system configured in the project can keep the generator sets running continuously and stably, not affected by light changes, and can also quickly participate in the peak regulation of the grid according to the peak and valley demand of the power grid.
After the project is fully completed, it can achieve an annual power generation of 198 million kWh, save more than 60,000 tons of standard coal, reduce emissions of more than 60 tons of sulfur dioxide, more than 60 tons of nitrogen oxides, about 20 tons of soot and more than 150,000 tons of carbon dioxide, and provide a steady stream of clean energy for the local area.
In addition, there is another silver "sunflower field" in the Shichengzi Photovoltaic Industrial Park in Hami City.
The Hamifu solar photovoltaic power station covers an area of more than 2,300 acres, and the 714 power generation equipment that has been built also rotates with the sun, always keeping the sunlight at a 90-degree right angle to the concentrating panel.
"We use dual-axis tracking concentrator power generation technology, and through unified integrated control, all power generation equipment will adjust the angle according to the height of the sun to maintain power generation efficiency. ”
Duan Mengqi, the station's director, said that under good weather conditions, the power generation technology can increase the efficiency of traditional photovoltaic power generation by about 20%.
In the first half of this year, the power station has generated more than 7 million kWh, supplementing the local electricity demand.
Shichengzi Photovoltaic Industrial Park is currently the largest single scale and the most complete photovoltaic module type in Xinjiang, with a total of 38 photovoltaic power generation projects and a total installed capacity of 820,000 kilowatts.
In the first half of this year, more than 110 million kWh of electricity was generated, an increase of 6% over the same period in 2019.
Hami is one of the regions with the best solar energy resources in China.
