Researchers in Brazil divided 667 patients from 55 hospitals across the country into three groups and conducted a clinical trial to compare the effects of hydroxychloroquine alone or in combination with other antibiotics azithromycin to see if it could help improve the condition of patients with mild and moderate COVID-19.
The results showed that hydroxychloroquine not only had no therapeutic effect, but could have damaging side effects on the organs.
The study was carried out by several leading hospitals in Brazil, such as Hospital Israelita Albert Einstein, Hospital of Heart Diseases (HCor), Hospital Sírio-Libanês, etc., in collaboration with the Brazilian Clinical Research Institute (BCRI) and the Brazilian Intensive Care Research Network (BRICNet).
