Yu'e Bao's income is down, but the "post-90s" are saving money with "revenge"?
With the decline in Yu'e Bao's income, the "post-90s" not only did not flee from Yu'e Bao, but began to save money "with a vengeance"?
According to the "Yu'e Bao Post-90s Money Saving Report" (2020 Edition) recently released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay, in the first half of the year, the "post-90s" love to save money more: the per capita amount of money saved increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90s" are more inclined to start saving from a "small amount of money", and sixty percent of them save an average of less than 20 yuan per transaction...
Saving money with Yue Bao has also become a money-saving habit for the "post-90s".
The data shows that among the 700 million Yu'e Bao users, 134 million users are "post-90s".
There are 174 million "post-90s" in China, that is to say, about 3 out of every 4 "post-90s" in the country are using Yu'e Bao to save money.
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of money market funds such as Yu Bao has fallen from more than 2% at the beginning of the year to about 1.5%.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of the "post-90s" to save money.
In the context of the improvement of Yu'e Bao's "money-saving effect", many young people who are accustomed to using Yu'e Bao have also been directly transformed into "basic people".
Alipay data shows that as of July 13, the new "basic people" on Alipay have more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu'e Bao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money market funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90s" girls are more inclined to save more money, with an average of 20% more money than men, and 6 percent of users who hold funds on the Alipay platform are men, and women tend to choose a more stable financial management method than men.
After saving money, what are the plans of the "post-90s"?
Alipay data shows that the "post-90s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, and the most users take travel as the goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90s" people have saved money to prepare for post-epidemic travel, and the resumption of cinemas has also provided a new way to shift from saving money to consumption.
