France increases military investment in space-Xinhuanet
French Defense Minister Florence Parly said on the 24th that France will add hundreds of millions of euros in space defense budget and develop space military forces to prevent other countries from "unfriendly moves" in outer space.
Parley told Le Provence on the same day that between 2019 and 2025, France's budget for spending on military space programs will increase from the previously proposed 3.6 billion euros (about 4.2 billion US dollars) to 4.3 billion euros (5 billion US dollars).
According to the French Military Planning Act 2019-2025, approved by the French parliament in 2018, France is expected to update its existing observation and communication satellites, launch three electromagnetic surveillance satellites, and modernize its space surveillance radar.
French President Emmanuel Macron announced last July that a space military command and an "aviation and space force" would be established within the French Air Force.
Parley said the space force would be officially announced later when she visited a military academy in Salon, Provence.
Parley said the space force is part of the Air Force and will have a strength of 500 by 2025.
"Gone are the old ideas that space served the common good of science," she said. Today, space is the arena of struggle for global supremacy. ”
Parley reiterated Macron's previous statement, saying that the French side has no intention of provoking an arms race.
"We are by no means engaged in an arms race. But it is incumbent upon me to fully recognize the threats we may face. ”
Parley recalled the 2017 surveillance of a military satellite shared by France and Italy.
She claimed that the "peeping" was a Russian satellite.
The Russian side denied this statement.
Parly said France would "soon" have small patrol satellites capable of detecting and pinpointing "the hands behind those unfriendly moves."
According to the French media, the reason why France seeks to establish a space force is because US President Donald Trump asked the US Department of Defense to draft a bill to establish a space force in February last year.
Trump signed the National Defense Authorization Act last December, approving the creation of the Space Force, the sixth largest branch of the U.S. military.
Some experts are worried that these US moves have accelerated the pace of US space militarization and may trigger a new round of space arms race.
Hohhot, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The reporter learned from the Haibo Bay Water Conservancy Hub Administration of the Yellow River that the Haibo Bay Water Conservancy Hub has actively resolved the No. 2 flood this year in the past few days, and as of the afternoon of the 26th, the amount of water coming from the upstream is the same as the amount of water coming out of the reservoir, the monitoring data are normal, and the flood is smoothly passing through the Wuhai section of the Yellow River in Inner Mongolia.
In order to cope with the flood process, the Haibo Bay Water Conservancy Hub of the Yellow River in Wuhai City, Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, gradually lowered the water level of the reservoir from 0:00 on July 23, and the outflow rate was controlled by no more than 3,000 cubic meters per second, until the water level in front of the dam dropped to 1,071 meters, freeing up the flood control reservoir capacity.
At the same time, the application of sand discharge dispatch was started.
In the past few days, the Haibo Bay Water Conservancy Hub Management Bureau of the Yellow River has paid close attention to the water situation and the development and changes of the flood season 24 hours a day, strengthened the operation of the reservoir and the safety management of the dam, and strengthened the inspection and protection of the left and right banks of the reservoir and important parts, especially the dangerous sections, to ensure the safety of the flood.
As of 17:00 on July 26, the inflow of the Haibo Bay Water Conservancy Hub was 2,760 cubic meters per second, the outflow was 2,760 cubic meters per second, and the water level in front of the dam was 1,071.5 meters.
At present, the flood gate dam section, earth-rock dam section and tailwater slope and other hydraulic structures are normal, the monitoring data fluctuate within the normal range, and the No. 2 flood of the Yellow River this year is smoothly passing through the Wuhai section of Inner Mongolia.
