According to the report, the shared accommodation market has been picking up since March-Chinanews.com
According to the "China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020" (hereinafter referred to as the "Report") released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the State Information Center a few days ago, due to the impact of the epidemic, in the first five months of 2020, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market fell by 72.1% year-on-year.
However, the shared accommodation market has been picking up since March, with market transactions, bookings and receptions gradually recovering.
According to the report, the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has dropped sharply, on the one hand, due to the sharp decline in demand for travel accommodation under the epidemic prevention and control, the number of orders has decreased sharply, the total number of orders in the first five months has decreased by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions has decreased by 63% year-on-year, on the other hand, the weak demand has also led to a more significant decline in room night prices, with the average room night price in the first five months falling by 16% year-on-year.
However, in March, April and May, the market transaction volume increased by 78%, 199% and 35% month-on-month respectively, the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% month-on-month respectively, and the number of visitors increased by 81%, 112% and 28% month-on-month respectively.
The report points out that the development of the shared accommodation industry is optimistic in the long run, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the State Information Center, told the "Workers' Daily" reporter that the development of shared accommodation needs more powerful policy support, on the one hand, it is necessary to do a good job in the implementation of the policies that have been introduced in the early stage, further strengthen the policy publicity and implementation, and focus on creating a better business environment;
