Chinanews.com, Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan, Zhang Shushan, Xu Jingyi) The Department of Vascular Surgery, Shanghai Changhai Hospital of the Naval Medical University, a famous vascular surgery center in China, signed a contract with the Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University on the 25th to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of aortic acute and critical disease.
According to Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University, after the vascular surgery department of the two hospitals officially formed a cooperative unit, it will carry out remote consultation, formulate a treatment plan with Changhai Hospital for real-time online consultation, select and send talents for further study and training, and jointly carry out weekly surgical technology exchanges and teaching rounds.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out innovative scientific research on surgery, science popularization and early screening of aortic disease, etc.
A special seminar on the aorta hosted by the Beijing Health Promotion Association and undertaken by Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University was held in Xiamen on the same day.
At the same time, the two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Xiamen held a signing ceremony for the Vascular Surgery Collaboration Center, announcing the formation of a cooperative unit to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
The Department of Vascular Surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital is the only vascular surgery institute in the whole army and the only clinical medical center for vascular diseases in Shanghai, as well as the first national key discipline of vascular surgery.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of the Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
The Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is the first independent discipline of vascular surgery in Fujian Province, which has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases, and was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty in 2018.
In the treatment of aortic disease, in addition to the treatment of dissection aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has rich experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
"The Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is very outstanding in the region in terms of the history of development, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of the operation, so we have established a collaborative center this time, in addition to the aorta, we can also carry out all-round in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of lower limb arteries, carotid arteries and other diseases. ”
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of the Department of Vascular Surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
In 2018, Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to establish the "Li Zhaoshen Famous Doctor Studio" in the Department of Gastroenterology.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of the vascular surgery department of the hospital, said in an interview with a reporter from Chinanews that the vascular surgery department of the hospital has also exchanged relations with Changhai Hospital for a long time, and the two hospitals have officially formed a cooperative unit, which has brought the cooperation and exchanges between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to Xiamen to carry out surgical technical exchanges, teaching ward rounds, and discussion of difficult cases, and at the same time further carry out remote consultations, which are currently planned to be held once a week.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the largest cause of death in China, and the aorta, as the main artery of various organs of the human body, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment, the thickest part of the aorta is up to 4cm in diameter, once a hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or vascular intima rupture produces dissection, which will cause massive bleeding, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyles and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the world's largest country with hypertension, and the number of aortic diseases has also increased.
Doctors can "re-lane" the blood flow by inserting a stent from the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta to avoid the impact of the aneurysm or ruptured dissection, and some procedures may even require only local anesthesia.
More than 10 domestic experts were invited to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic disease, and to carry out cutting-edge technology training and difficult case discussions in the form of conference salons.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic disease continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
