The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area was completed-Chinanews.com
2020-07-26 17:34:48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Little Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
Chinanews.com, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the small Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zhengwan high-speed railway, which is about 18.9 kilometers long, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Little Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 km/h in the projects currently under construction in China.
Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is located in Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, connecting Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railways in the north of Zhengzhou, and reaching Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou.
The small Three Gorges Tunnel of the Zhengwan high-speed railway was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows the breakthrough site.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway starts from Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and goes southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City, with a total length of about 818 kilometers and a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the section from Zhengzhou to Xiangyang has been put into operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The small Three Gorges Tunnel, which was completed on the 26th, is a control project of the Zhengwan high-speed railway, which is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County, Chongqing, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and the entire line was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, the person in charge of the design of the Zhengwan high-speed railway tunnel of China Railway Second Institute Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the terrain and geological conditions of the small Three Gorges Tunnel are very complex, facing the risks of karst, mud inrush, and large deformation of soft rock, and it is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and the tunnel design and construction are extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we adopted geological survey method, geophysical prospecting method and advanced drilling method to advance geological forecasting, and adopted special design schemes for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a 24-meter-long bridge was designed and built to cross a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement. Wang Guojun said.
According to the construction party China Railway Tunnel Bureau, during the construction of the tunnel, the combination of dredging and plugging was adopted, through the construction of horizontal tunnel flat guide, grouting and water blocking, strengthening the tunnel structure support and the construction of sewage treatment station, which not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Little Three Gorges Scenic Area, and successfully overcame the bad geology such as the large deformation of soft rock up to 7 kilometers long, and the construction problems such as multi-sudden mud water gushing with a maximum daily water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the completion and opening of the Zhengwan high-speed railway, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger transport main channel from southwest China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China, which is of great significance for improving the capacity and quality of the northeast railway channel in southwest China, improving the layout of regional road network, accelerating the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the line, promoting regional coordinated development, and promoting the implementation of the strategy of western development.
