Employment and prices are generally stable, showing that the economy has "temperature"
Economic Daily, China Economic Net reporter Lin Huocan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China coordinated the promotion of epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development, the epidemic prevention and control situation continued to improve, the steady economic recovery trend was obvious, and the employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate rose.
In particular, in February, the production and business activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of suspension of production, the demand for labor in enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in urban areas increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the order of production and life in the whole society has been continuously restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further strengthens macroeconomic policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting enterprises to stabilize jobs and expand employment.
China has increased policy hedging to stabilize jobs, played a combination of "reduction, exemption, and repatriation" policy, reduced or exempted the payment of three social insurance units in stages, allowed to postpone the payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of the policy of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, and provided absorption subsidies and internship subsidies for enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various employment stabilization policies, the employment demand of enterprises has rebounded steadily, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in urban areas has gradually declined, with the surveyed unemployment rate of 5.7% in June.
Zhang Yi, director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to take effect, and the labor force that withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic in the early stage returned one after another, and the urban labor force participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the level of the same period last year.
According to the data, total urban employment increased by more than 19% in June compared with February, with most industries reaching pre-pandemic levels, and the average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and slightly 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, a multi-year high.
Entering February, although the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, which is not only driven by consumer demand before the Spring Festival, but also by the staggered month of the Spring Festival and the low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the coronavirus pandemic on prices has been particularly pronounced.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, in January and February, there were logistics delays, untimely supply of materials, and increased transportation costs across the country.
In order to cope with the disruption of the price situation caused by epidemic prevention and control, the relevant departments have included important daily necessities in the scope of emergency transportation to ensure the smooth transportation of materials.
Under the effect of a series of policy measures, the supply of vegetables and fruits in the market has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government introduced the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, the supply of pork reserves was significantly improved, the production capacity of pigs was restored in an orderly manner, and the order of production and marketing gradually normalized.
Since March, pork prices have continued to decline, driving the year-on-year increase in food prices to fall to 10.6% in May, and in June, pork prices rose slightly month-on-month due to factors such as the slowdown in pig slaughter, the reduction in imports and the rebound in group consumption demand.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices was obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high base of comparison in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruit continued to decline year-on-year, with an average decrease of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the masses has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all localities have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, the CPI has declined month-on-month for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also fallen from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the price level has generally returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflationary pressure is not large, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and life order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
We should effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in the main producing areas of grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on hoarding, price gouging, and other behaviors that disrupt market order.
