In the first half of the year, the crime of telecommunications network fraud rose by seventy, and the Supreme People's Procuratorate summarized the characteristics-Chinanews.com
Chinanews.com, July 26 According to the website of the Supreme People's Procuratorate, in the first half of this year, procuratorial organs across the country prosecuted a total of 58,101 people for fraud, an increase of 35% year-on-year.
In particular, among the crimes of obstructing epidemic prevention and control, fraud crimes are frequent, and the number of fraud crimes prosecuted by procuratorial organs accounts for 43.4% of all crimes that impede epidemic prevention and control.
The Supreme People's Procuratorate has carried out targeted guidance, and has released a total of 9 of the 10 batches of typical cases related to epidemic prevention and control, involving the crime of fraud.
Judging from the handling of cases by the procuratorial organs in the first half of the year, there are many types of fraud crimes, ranging from national macro policies to the clothing, food, housing and transportation of the people, including epidemic-related fraud, "medical trust" fraud, "health care products" fraud, "enrollment intermediary" fraud, "routine loan" fraud, deception of state subsidies fraud, national asset unfreezing fraud, etc., constantly "pushing through the old and bringing forth the new", covering education, medical care, employment, pension, social security, land requisition and demolition, targeted poverty alleviation, etc. Many fields, such as finance and credit, not only cause economic losses to victims, but also seriously affect economic and social development.
In particular, some telecommunication network frauds break through the restrictions of national borders, regions, and personnel, and have the characteristics of stakeholders, cross-border, remote, and electronic payments, and there are many unspecified victim groups, and the harm is great.
For example, some set up special companies, rent high-end office buildings, set up multiple departments or positions, use legal network platforms to publicize and recruit, train and assess recruiters, and adopt enterprise operation mode management, wearing a "legal coat", which is more confusing.
It is the bounden duty of the procuratorial organs to punish and prevent crimes in accordance with the law and to promptly issue early warnings to the public and relevant departments.
In the judicial handling of cases, the procuratorial organs conscientiously perform their duties, not only insisting on maintaining a high-pressure posture against fraud crimes, but also detailing various law enforcement measures in a targeted manner, and promoting social governance through the formulation and issuance of procuratorial recommendations.
The procuratorial organs strictly control the facts, evidence, procedures, and application of law in fraud cases of arrest and prosecution, and take the facts as the basis and the law as the criterion, so as to ensure that nothing is done in vain.
In particular, for telecommunications network fraud crimes, pay attention to the central role of electronic data in the determination of facts, and strive to build an evidence chain that corroborates electronic data, verbal evidence, and documentary evidence.
For example, in the case of epidemic-related fraud handled by the Yinzhou District Procuratorate of Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, the procuratorate intervened in advance as soon as possible, and it took only 5 days from the occurrence of the case to the conclusion of the case, reflecting the attitude and determination to handle it quickly and strictly and maintain the overall stability of the society.
In the process of reviewing arrests and examining for prosecution, attention was paid to the prosecution of omitted offenders in cases, correcting the omissions of 733 arrests by the public security organs, and correcting the omissions of the public security organs to review and prosecute 1,113 co-defendants.
In the first half of the year, procuratorial organs across the country issued 298 procuratorial recommendations on fraud crimes, promoting joint efforts to prevent fraud crimes and promote in-depth governance.
For example, in response to the loopholes in the supervision of telecommunications networks discovered in the handling of cases, the Guangzhou Municipal Procuratorate and the Dongguan Municipal Procuratorate of Guangdong Province promptly put forward procuratorial suggestions, urging relevant units to strengthen supervision, improve mechanisms, and promote the construction of long-term systems.
Fourth, we should make every effort to do a good job in recovering stolen goods and recovering losses.
Procuratorial organs in all localities have grasped important links such as intervening in the investigation, guiding the collection of evidence, and reviewing for prosecution, urging the investigating organs to actively recover stolen money, cooperating with relevant departments to do a good job of recovering stolen goods and recovering losses, and striving to minimize the economic losses caused by fraud to the people.
For example, in the case of Lin Moumou's routine loan handled by the Beijing Municipal Procuratorate, which involved 22 properties waiting to be sealed, under the circumstance that the real estate may be disposed of in advance by other cases, it was the first to formulate and issue a "Letter of Suspension of Enforcement" and send it to the relevant court in a timely manner, suggesting that the court that had previously sealed the property should suspend the execution of the real estate involved in the case, and deal with it uniformly after the facts of the crime were clarified, so as to make the greatest efforts to recover the real estate involved in the case and recover the victim's losses.
The prosecutor reminded everyone to be very vigilant against fraud crimes, not to expect "pie in the sky", and not to be gullible if they think it is cheap, and to guard their "money bags".
