Weining County, where the town is located, has a certain reputation in the surrounding areas because of its low latitude, high altitude, sufficient sunlight, large temperature difference between day and night, high sugar content and good taste, but it has not been able to sell at a good price and has not been able to form an industrial scale because of its small size and many spots.
The town used to be a poor township with "spring and autumn potatoes", and the local poverty incidence rate was as high as 25.8% 10 years ago.
In the critical period when poverty alleviation has entered a decisive battle, it is urgent to change traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure, and increase farmers' income.
After many visits, Chen Chao, Secretary of the Party Committee of Huana Town, and a group of people in the town believe that industrial development can no longer take the old road.
To this end, the town of Rina has introduced leading enterprises to grow apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Beyond Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Huana Town from Shaanxi in 2015 to investigate, and immediately took a fancy to the local planting conditions, and began to plant apple trees in the local area in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees, and Li Yuanzhong and his wife muttered in their hearts: "I have planted apples for so many years, and I haven't seen anyone in the village who has made a fortune by planting apples." ”
"The apples that are planted are dwarfed, so they don't make the tree grow too tall. ”
What Li Yuanzhong didn't expect was that a new method was adopted for apple planting this time, the irrigation pipe was laid under each apple tree, and the water and fertilizer were poured to the roots of the tree.
At present, the apple base has gradually entered the bumper production period, and the market is as Hou Jianwen expected, apples are not worried about selling, and are deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life, although he is still farming, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 acres of land transferred to the apple base, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee every year, there are profit dividends after hanging the fruit, the couple usually work in the base, "one person can get 80 yuan a day, and there is work all year round."
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividends were more than 2,800 yuan, plus land transfer fees and the couple's labor income, the family's income was more than 80,000 yuan.
"At present, the initial results have been achieved, and the annual output value of 1 mu of apples is more than 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of corn. ”
Chen Chao told reporters that 20,000 acres of apples have been planted in the town, 6,000 acres in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 farmers and 17,200 people, including 656 poor households and 2,952 people, and more than 6 million yuan in wages a year.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets were bulging day by day, also began to realize his "wish".
During the Lunar New Year this year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle and drove a car to and from work every day, "There are still more than a dozen acres of land at home, and when the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of them will be transferred to them, and the income will be more." ”
