Membrane separation technology helps solve the "greenhouse effect" - Chinanews.com
Membrane separation technology helps solve the "greenhouse effect"
Schematic diagram of a novel hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology
Recently, the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University has made significant progress in the "membrane separation method to capture carbon dioxide", and successfully developed a new hybrid matrix membrane preparation technology, which greatly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
The results have been published as a cover article in the international journal Greenhouse Gases: Science and Technology.
The "greenhouse effect" is a major environmental problem that plagues human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit of the "greenhouse effect".
How to efficiently capture and use carbon dioxide emitted by humans is the focus of scientists.
"Membrane separation" is an emerging carbon dioxide capture technology, which separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, and has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving, and simple operation.
How to make the membrane material "breathe deeply" and improve the gas separation efficiency is the bottleneck and difficulty of capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas and explored the influence of different solvents on the separation performance of membrane gas through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that the carbon nanotubes in the membrane material are more uniformly distributed and "more breathable" by using N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of the hybrid matrix membranes prepared by this new technology is close to the upper limit of the current theoretical separation of such membrane materials.
"The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation. ”
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team at Tianjin University, said: "We hope that this technology can provide strong support for the treatment of flue gas in coal-fired power plants and chemical enterprises in the future, and play a significant role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions. ”
Before volunteering to fill in, first understand what is the professional grade difference-Chinanews.com
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
Before volunteering, understand what is the professional grade
Every year, students or parents fill in the college entrance examination because they do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary application, which in turn affects the voluntary application.
This year, five universities, Beijing Jiaotong University, University of Science and Technology Beijing, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology, jointly released the 2020 enrollment policy to cancel the professional grade difference.
What does professional grade mean and what is the significance of volunteering?
There are three ways to assign rules
Experts remind that before filling in the volunteers, you must read the "Enrollment Regulations" of your favorite school carefully to understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of file adjustment, major allocation rules, etc.
The major allocation rules refer to the three main ways of admitting majors: major priority, score priority, and major grade difference after colleges and universities adjust their files.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be clarified in the Enrollment Regulations.
However, there are also some colleges and universities where the admission principle is that the total score is preferred, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, the candidates within the admission range will be lined up according to the total score, and when the score does not reach the admission score line of the first professional choice, it will be seen whether the admission score line of the second professional choice is reached, and so on until the last professional choice is admitted, and there is no grade difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called "professional grade difference" means that when the college arranges the candidates' majors, they determine the admission majors of the candidates who choose to apply for different majors according to one or several score values announced in the enrollment regulations, and this kind of score value is the "professional grade difference".
That is, the difference between the scores of the first professional and non-first professional preferences of the candidates, and the score difference between the professional preferences, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example:
Suppose that student Xiao Ming applied for college A and scored 560 points, and his professional preferences were: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e-commerce, and the professional admission of college A implements the method of professional grade difference, and the grade difference is 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 points.
If he is not admitted to Computer Science, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and the candidates who apply for "International Trade" will be ranked according to the score of 558 to determine whether they meet the admission requirements of the major; if they still cannot meet the requirements, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e., 557 points) for the third professional choice If they still can't meet the requirements, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (i.e., 556 points) for admission to the fourth major, and if the subsequent majors still can't meet their professional aspirations, the points will not be deducted, and so on.
Different universities have different professional grade differences
With the popularity of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have now canceled the professional grade difference, but this year there are still some colleges and universities still retain this method, from the "Enrollment Regulations" published by each school, this year there are more than 20 universities set up the professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, Civil Aviation Flight University of China, etc.
Within these universities, each university has a different level of specialization.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University, and candidates whose files have been submitted to the school will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in their professional preferences by 1 point and then sorted by score.
However, some universities set different professional grade differences between different majors.
For example, in Jimei University, the total score difference of professional volunteers is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, and there is no grade difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteers, and the professional grade difference between other professional volunteers and adjustment professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in the volunteers, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the school they are applying for, to see if there is a professional grade difference, what is the form of the grade difference, while fully considering the scores, but also to reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected, if the institution in the enrollment regulations clearly adopt the score difference method for admission, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major, and improve the admission chance.
